    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Religion of ancient India based in the more ancient Vedism. It is characterized by a strong veneration for the priestly class, the Brahmans, devotional worship (bhakti), and the popularity and prominence of the individual deities, Siva and Vishnu.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000075924/Williams, Religious Thought and Life in India (1883)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a la religión de la antigua India basada en el Vedismo. Se caracteriza por una fuerte veneración por la clase sacerdotal, los Brahmanes, culto devocional (bhakti), y la popularidad y preponderancia de las deidades individuales, Siva and Vishnu.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de religie in het oude India die haar oorsprong vindt in de Vedische religie. Wordt gekenmerkt door een sterke verering van de geestelijken (de brahmanen), devotie (bhakti) en de populariteit van de afzonderlijke goden Shiva en Visjnoe.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以吠陀教為基礎的古印度宗教。特色為極尊敬僧侶階級與婆羅門階級、虔誠敬拜(bhakti, 對神的虔信)、有多個神明受到歡迎並具有聲望，如濕婆及毗濕奴。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
